'''AS ADEMA Analamanga''' is a Malagasy football club based in [[Antananarivo]],<ref>[http://www.sport-madagascar.com/association-sportive-malgache.html Sport Madagascar: AS Adema is based in Antananarivo (in French)]</ref> [[Madagascar]]. They have won the [[THB Champions League]] championship on three occasions, in 2002, 2006 and 2012. In 2002 they also advanced to the quarterfinals of the [[CAF Cup]] before losing to [[Al-Masry]] of [[Egypt]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/afcup02.html African Club Competitions 2002<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

AS ADEMA won a [[THB Champions League]] match against [[SO l'Emyrne]] by the score of [[AS Adema 149-0 SO l'Emyrne|149–0]] on October 31, 2002.  SOE scored 149 [[own goal]]s in protest of a refereeing decision.<ref>[http://espn.go.com/soccer/news/2002/1102/1454712.html ESPN.com&nbsp;– SOCCER&nbsp;– Team repeatedly scores own goals to protest refs<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

