[[Image:USAWheelchairRugbyLogo.png|right|250px]]
The '''United States Quad Rugby Association (USQRA)''' is a [[non-profit organization]] and the [[sports governing body|governing body]] for [[wheelchair rugby]] in the [[United States]].  The organization represents the United States in [[International Wheelchair Rugby Federation|IWRF]] and the [[United States national wheelchair rugby team|national wheelchair rugby team]] in the [[United States Paralympic Committee]]. The USQRA's President is Gary Pate.

The organization is responsible for the selection and training of the team that represent the United States in international tournaments, including the [[World Wheelchair Rugby Championships|IWRF World Championships]] and [[Wheelchair rugby at the Summer Paralympics|Games of the Paralympiad]] and the [[IWRF Americas Championship|qualifiers]] therefor, as well as for the promotion of the sport amongst prospective players, [[spectator sports|spectator]]s, and [[fan (aficionado)|fan]]s.

